data.current_description: Applies one or more updates to the document. Each request is validated before being applied. If any request is not valid, then the entire request will fail and nothing will be applied. Some requests have replies to give you some information about how they are applied. Other requests do not need to return information; these each return an empty reply. The order of replies matches that of the requests. For example, suppose you call batchUpdate with four updates, and only the third one returns information. The response would have two empty replies, the reply to the third request, and another empty reply, in that order. Because other users may be editing the document, the document might not exactly reflect your changes: your changes may be altered with respect to collaborator changes. If there are no collaborators, the document should reflect your changes. In any case, the updates in your request are guaranteed to be applied together atomically.
data.summary_suggestion: Apply multiple updates to a Google Docs document
data.description_suggestion: Applies one or more updates to a specified Google Docs document atomically. All updates are validated before application; if any update is invalid, the entire batch fails and no changes are applied. Updates are processed in order and return replies corresponding to each request (some updates return information, others return empty replies). Changes are applied atomically and guaranteed to succeed together. Note: concurrent edits by collaborators may alter how changes are reflected in the final document. Requires authentication and edit permissions.
